Date: 0/0/1966
Source: Encyclopaedia of New Zealand, An
Author: McLINTOCK
Vol / Page: 3/689
Edition:
Quote: A small bird of similar colouring and size [to the rock wren], but of a different genus, <i> Traversia lyallii </i>, now extinct, was known as the Stephen Island wren. Several specimens of this bird were recorded in 1894, but it has not been seen since.
